# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Warehouse repo .gitignore
#
# Principle: only commit the SOURCE of the pipeline (notebooks, lib/, scripts,
# seeds, overrides, docs). Everything else is regenerable from upstream APIs
# and lives on disk between runs (locally or in the GHA Actions cache).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── ephemeral data ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Raw upstream API caches — 800MB+ and growing. Restored from GHA cache between
# runs; never in git.
data/raw/

# Pipeline outputs are COMMITTED as a bootstrap baseline (~40MB across 75 files).
# This solves the cold-start dependency cascade — when GHA spins up a fresh
# runner with no warm cache, the hourly notebooks would otherwise fail trying to
# load wc26_nations / wc26_matches / referee_master / ... which only the frozen
# + daily buckets produce. Committing the baseline means a normal hourly run
# always has its dependencies on disk; refresh.py overwrites the parquets with
# fresher versions during the run, and the GHA cache carries those to the next
# tick. Local edits update the baseline naturally on commit.
# (Earlier this folder was ignored; the cold-start cascade in the first GHA
# runs forced this change.)
# data/processed/

# The emitted JSON folder is a build artifact of _emit_pwa_json.py — gets
# regenerated every run, never committed.
data/processed/json/

# .last_daily_run is just a marker file (date string only) that refresh.py
# uses to gate the once-per-day daily bundle. Regenerated automatically;
# ignored to avoid daily commit churn.
data/.last_daily_run

# .event_state.json IS committed as a baseline (tracks per-match/round status)
# so cache evictions don't regress the event-driven gating to "everything is
# newly finished". It updates every successful run, so commits will show diffs
# when you push local refreshes — that's expected.
# data/.event_state.json

# ── python / jupyter byproducts ──────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ── virtualenvs / IDE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.venv/
venv/
.env
.env.local
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store

# ── notebook execution outputs ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# refresh.py re-executes notebooks in place and writes outputs back. We DON'T
# commit those (they'd be massive churn on every run); strip with nbstripout
# locally before committing notebook edits. The GHA runner doesn't commit
# notebooks back at all — only pushes JSON to the PWA repo.
# (Notebooks themselves are tracked; this is just a reminder.)
